Kenya’s Economy Had ‘Major Slowdown’ on Climbing Oil Prices, Minister Says

-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 
2011-05-20T06:47:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/kenya-s-economy-had-major-slowdown-on-climbing-oil-prices-minister-says.html
Rising international oil prices since
July 2010 have led to “a major slowdown in  Kenya ’s economic
performance” and a “steep increase” in the cost of
living, Energy Minister Kiraitu Murungi said.  “Sometime we feel we are in a trap,” Murungi said today
at a conference in Nairobi, the capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah McGregor in Nairobi at 
 smcgregor5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
